      <div xml:id="NA117-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu varaivu nīṭa āṟṟāḷāya talaivi vaṉpoṟai (ER, ET: vaṉpuṟai) etiraḻintu colliyatu. 2. ciṟaippuṟamumām.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is what SHE, who was unable to bear it when the marriage was delayed, said in the face of being comforted. 2. Behind the fence.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA117">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            peruṅkaṭaṉ muḻaṅkak kāṉaṉ malara</l>
<l>            viruṅkaḻi yōta milliṟantu malira </l>
<l>            vaḷḷitaḻ neytal kūmpap puḷḷuṭaṉ</l>
<l>            kamaḻpūm potumpark kaṭci cērac</l>
<l>            celcuṭar maḻuṅkac civantuvāṅku maṇṭilaṅ </l>
<l>            kalcērpu naṇṇip paṭaraṭaipu naṭuṅkap</l>
<l>            pulampoṭu vanta puṉkaṇ mālai</l>
<l>            yaṉṉa ruṉṉār kaḻiyiṟ paṉṉāḷ</l>
<l>            vāḻaleṉ vāḻi tōḻi yeṉkaṭ</l>
<l>            piṇipiṟi tākak kūṟuvar </l>
<l>            paḻipiṟi tākal paṇpumā raṉṟē.</l>
    </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>I won't live, friend,</l>
<l rend="indent">for many days, if they pass by without his thinking the same way,</l>
<l rend="indent2">on sorrowful evening that has come with loneliness</l>
<l rend="indent3">so that one shivers, affliction settling<note place="foot">The use of the absolutive is strange but not really unfamiliar here: we probably have to read a new subject, i.e. <term xml:lang="ta">paṭar</term> for <term xml:lang="ta">aṭaipu</term>, and then again <term xml:lang="ta">maṇṭilam</term> for <term xml:lang="ta">naṇṇi</term>, while <term xml:lang="ta">civantu</term> decidedly should be <term xml:lang="ta">civanta</term>. T.V.G. even would prefer <term xml:lang="ta">naṇṇiya</term> to <term xml:lang="ta">naṇṇi</term>.</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent4">as the curved disk comes close, joining the stones<note place="foot">Actually we have two absolutives here for the setting of the sun, <term xml:lang="ta">cērpu</term> and <term xml:lang="ta">naṇṇi</term>. Perhaps one refers to the direct location (behind the western mountains), and one to the sun’s coming close to the earth.</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent4">turning red so that the going glow is [but] blunt,</l>
<l rend="indent">while the great sea thunders, the seashore grove is blossoming,</l>
<l rend="indent">while the flood from the dark backwaters traverses [and] floods the houses,</l>
<l rend="indent">while the many-petalled blue waterlilies close,</l>
<l rend="indent">while the birds together join [their] nests in the grove of fragrant flowers.</l>
<l>The say that the illness in me [is] something different.</l>
<l>It is not, however(?)<note place="foot">However" is an attempt at rendering the particle –<term xml:lang="ta">umār</term>, the valence of which is still unclear.</note>, of a kind that has another cause.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
